; These tests aim at verifying that gender and number are honored in messages
; relating to wearable items, both for the items and their wearer/carrier.
; ==============================================================================
; INVENTORY
; ==============================================================================
inventario
; ==============================================================================
; EXAMINING NPCs
; ==============================================================================
x vendedor
x mujer
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; PLURAL NPCs
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; We need to ensure that plural NPCs are also mentioned correctly...
x mellizos
x mellizas
; ==============================================================================
; EXAMINE NPC: WORN ITEMS MESSAGE GNA
; ==============================================================================
; We need to check that the 'examine' message for listing worn items correctly
; matches the gender and number of "puesto" depending on the items contents.
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Mixed Gender Items
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; If the list contains both masculine and feminine items: "puestos" (m.p.)
x vendedor
; If the list contains only masculine items: "puestos" (m.p.)
x mellizos
; If the list contains only feminine items: "puestas" (f.p.)
toma traje
x vendedor
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Single Items
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; If the list contains only a single masculine item: "puesto" (m.s.)
x mujer
; If the list contains only a single feminine item: "puesta" (f.s.)
x mellizas
; ==============================================================================
; LISTING NPCs
; ==============================================================================
; Since the EXAMINA and INVENTARIO commands don't rely on the LIST statement,
; but use custom coded loops to separate carried and worn items, we've added
; to this test adventure the special verb LIST <ACTOR> to check that the LIST
; statement correctly mentions worn items as being worn according to GNA.
list hero
list vendedor
list mujer
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; PLURAL NPCs
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
list mellizos
list mellizas
